message.content:
We start by extracting the key numbers from the three statements.

1. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio and Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 • Operating Cash Flow (from the cash flow statement) = –18,924,462.44  
 • Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 1,015,922.54  
  Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
   = –18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54 ≈ –18.63  

(In the sample the “Operating Cash Flow Ratio” was identical to the “Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio.”)

2. Debt to Equity Ratio  
 • Here “Debt” is taken as the Total Current Liabilities (no non‐current debt items are shown): 1,015,922.54  
 • Total Owner’s Equity (from the balance sheet) = 29,842,166.21  
  Debt to Equity = 1,015,922.54 / 29,842,166.21 ≈ 0.0341  
  Rounding we report this as 0.03

3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
 • Total Revenue from the income statement = 20,318,450.67  
 • Total Assets (end) from the balance sheet = 30,858,088.75  
  Total Asset Turnover = 20,318,450.67 / 30,858,088.75 ≈ 0.6584  
  Rounded to 0.66

4. Quick Ratio  
 • Quick Assets = Current Assets – Inventory  
  = 20,314,894.50 – 9,100,000.00 = 11,214,894.50  
 • Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 11,214,894.50 / 1,015,922.54 ≈ 11.04

5. Return on Equity (ROE)  
 • Net Profit from the income statement = 1,842,166.21  
 • Total Owner’s Equity = 29,842,166.21  
  ROE = (Net Profit / Total Equity) × 100  
  = (1,842,166.21 / 29,842,166.21) × 100 ≈ 6.17%

6. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
 • From the balance sheet: beginning Accounts Receivable = 0; ending Accounts Receivable = 12,792,007.89  
  Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 12,792,007.89) / 2 = 6,396,003.945  
 • Accounts Receivable Turnover = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 20,318,450.67 / 6,396,003.945 ≈ 3.177  
  Rounded to 3.18

Thus, the final answer is:

    "Quick Ratio": "11.04",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-18.63",
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.17%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "3.18"
  }
}
